Remove NO_OPs from a List

Source: R/NO_OP.R

Remove all NO_OP elements from a list.

filter_noop(x)

Arguments

x

list
List to filter.

Value

list: The input list, with all NO_OP elements removed.

See also

Other Path Branching: NO_OP, is_noop, mlr_pipeop_branch, mlr_pipeop_unbranch
